# WordPress Production & Release Rule

No version is complete until **all seven** criteria are true. Do not ask whether to apply this rule — it is mandatory for every version.

## Version Completion Checklist (7 required)

1. **Git Commit completed** — focused diff; no secrets; follow repo commit style.
2. **Git Push completed** — branch pushed to remote.
3. **WordPress ZIP generated** — single root folder `yooy-ai-studio/`; forward-slash paths; includes `plugin/`, bundled `modules/`, `providers/`, `assets/`, `templates/`.
4. **ZIP installs successfully on PHP 7.4** — upload/extract to `wp-content/plugins/` without error.
5. **Plugin activates without Fatal Error** — no parse/redeclare/missing-file fatals on activation.
6. **All modules load successfully** — 14 modules registered; core boot completes.
7. **Main dashboard opens successfully** — admin menu `YooY AI Studio` and shortcode shell load without error.

Also produce before marking complete:

- **Activation Audit Report** — pass `scripts/audit-activation.ps1` (missing requires, duplicate classes/methods, PHP 8 syntax = 0).
- **Release Notes** — version, changes, install steps, PHP/WP requirements.

## Pre-Commit / Pre-Push Gate

Every release MUST pass before commit and push:

| Check | Command / Script |
|-------|------------------|
| PHP 7.4 compatibility | `scripts/audit-activation.ps1` (PHP 8-only syntax scan) |
| JS syntax | `node --check` on all staged `*.js` |
| WordPress activation audit | `scripts/audit-activation.ps1` |
| Package build | `scripts/build-wordpress-package.ps1` |

Default PHP 7.4 ZIP name pattern: `yooy-ai-studio-{version}-php74.zip`

## Target Environment

- **WordPress:** 6.x
- **PHP:** 7.4 (minimum; e.g. Whois hosting 7.4.33)
- Plugin header: `Requires PHP: 7.4`

## Scope

- Activation fixes and compatibility only when unblocking release — no new features during hotfix builds.
- Applies automatically to all future OpenStudio / YooY AI Studio versions.
